ol.li: Devices attached to an SDN switch generate traffic. They can be servers or clients and don't need to be aware of Poseidon in any way.
An SDN controller (BCF or Faucet) provides the management and visibility of devices on the SDN switch(es).
Poseidon learns about new devices on the network from the SDN controller.
If the devices are unknown, Poseidon tells the controller to start collecting traffic it sees from those new devices.
That collected traffic gets forwarded to Poseidon via designated (switch) mirror port

Poseidon analyzes ingested traffic using Machine Learning techniques to first classify what kind of device it is, and subsequently if it is acting normal or abnormal for that class of device. Results are sent to Poseidon's logs.
All of the results and learned devices are then visualized using CRviz.
